Hi Frank,

: This is just a small question, for which I can't find the answer right away:
: Is anybody out there running Linux on a Pentium ? If so, have
: any problems in installing and getting it to work been encountered ?

I have a P-60 board with the mercury-3 chipset and have no problems. It runs
as stable as my old board used to run. But it is much faster. The NCR SCSI
chip is also no problem.

Be sure to get a board with revision 3 of the chipset. This version is more
bug-free than the older versions.


